Metaphor vs Simile

Mechanistically, they’re more different than English class usually teaches.

Simile

A is like B.

The source and target remain separate.

Tree ----comparison----> Network

You borrow a few properties.

Low coupling.

Easy to discard.

Low reconstruction cost.

⸻

Metaphor

A is B.

Now the structures partially merge.

Tree
   \
    Semantic Merge
   /
Network

The target begins inheriting mechanisms.

Suddenly:

branches

roots

growth

decay

pruning

fruit

seasonality

all become computational operators.

That’s why metaphors are so much more powerful.

They’re operator transfer, not just description.

